description: AÂ seemingly minor alteration of the timestream is causing major changes. January and Jughead investigate and trace the source to an earlier goof by Jughead himself. While sleepwalking and dreaming of pasta, he had eaten a few Chinese noodles from the 13th century. Unfortunately they were the only samples available to Marco Polo to bring to Europe.
January and Jughead travel back to Arthurian times to face a time-traveler with world-conquering ambitions: Morgan Le Fay

Hot Dog accidentaly uses Jughead's time-traveling device and is lost in the timestream, ending up in random times and locations. The Time Police agents from various eras are alarmed and call a meeting to discuss solutions to the situation. Everyone certain that the situation is extremely dangerous. Jughead and January have to resolve the problem. But it could also be their last mission. They will be blamed for every misshap occuring and their resignations called for.

January and Jughead have to resolve a situation in modern-day Riverdale. The city is about to be destroyed by a flood. But Jughead's records from the future reports the city largely surviving. To resolve the contradiction, the duo have to rescue Riverdale.Â 
Â 
January first meets Archie in person. Reggie tries to charm her but she finds him annoying.

Jughead has been studying the history of the American Civil War (1861 - 1865). He is particularly interested in the Battle of Riverdale. A Union force defending the city was about to fall to a Confederate invasion force. But a mysterious Colonel Pickens appeared from nowhere, led a successful counterattack, before dissappearing. Modern Riverdale hoors him as a hero. Studying images of the man, Jughead realized why he looked familiar: Pickens was Jughead in disguise. Time to travel back towards the War and play his part in the battlefield.Â  Or else the Confederates will capture a guest to Riverdale, Abraham Lincoln, and the War will take a different course.

Morgan Le Fay escapes incarceration in the Time Police headquarters. She decides to take revenge on Jughead by derailing his own personal timeline. But she ends up facing different versions of her enemy.
The brand-new era in Ben 10 continues! ACTION PACK has three all-new Ben 10 Ultimate Alien stories filled with the usual blend of action, adventure, comedy and out-of-this-world excitement!
name: Ben 10 On Ice; Breaking News; Star Chaser

description: Dawg's missing without his leash! It's up to Foghorn the C.S.I chicken to find him. And he has two suspects: Henry Hawk and the WEASEL! This mystery's sure to leave you laughing!

description: Julia Diggers has delayed the final stage of her students' training for long enough! Carla, Luan and Gar must enter the mystic Proving Grounds created by the founders of their martial art. The labyrinth of trials is designed to test the strength and will of students on the edge of mastery. But something is amiss within: A band of pint-sized, emerald-clad invaders have usurped the grounds' mystical forces and reformed them into an impenetrable baffle of deadly traps!

The New World is turning out to be more than Angel bargained for as he's confronted with a monstrous, mythical beast, and continues to try and find a "cure" for his painful new soul. But when the earth begins to shake, Angel finds himself facing the cause of one histories great "natural" disasters.

IDW's newly recolored reprints of classic Doctor Who tales from years past continues in this all-new series, featuring the Sixth Doctor! Steve Parkhouse and John Ridgway present "Polly the Glot," featuring an all-new cover by Robert Hack (Grant Morrison's Doctor Who) and new colors by Charlie Kirchoff.
name: Polly the Glot, Part One

description: Chaos descends upon the stage, as the city crumbles into a ravaged wasteland. Loki has bested the fallen angel Sirian-and seized Lyra Constance for his own. Or has he? As the curtains lift-and the sounds surge-Loki may have grabbed hold of more than he bargained for. Guest starring Doc Coyle & God Forbid.

A dangerous political situation is about to explode in the capital city of Venezuela and the only Joe who can help is... SNOW JOB?! Outgunned and out of his element, can Snow Job possibly succeed in a sniper battle on the dangerous rooftops of Caracas?

Captain John Harriman is the commander of the USS Enterprise B. He is also the man many hold responsible for the mysterious disappearance and presumed death of James Tiberius Kirk, the renowned Starfleet captain by whom all others are judged. How does a man recover from killing a legend? Find out in this very special issue!

Guest starring Dr. Leonard "Bones" McCoy.

Coney Island isn't the best place to fight off flesh-eating zombie masses, but when there is no more room downtown, the ladies must run to the beach. After Mirah and Fanya befriend a group of sideshow freaks, simmering group tensions come to a boil as inflamed zombies break into their fancy hotel refuge. Zombies on fire!

From the creative minds of Image partners Robert Kirkman & Marc Silvestri! Todd Carey is recovering from a nasty divorce, his daughter is flunking out of college and he's just learned that his father has been diagnosed with Alzheimer's. Unable to really take care of himself, Todd has allowed his father to move in with him. What Todd doesn't know, is that his father is the masked vigilante STEALTH... and has been his entire life. Stealth has many enemies and his erratic behavior could easily get him killed--and all this trouble falls squarely in Todd's lap.Â

name: Heart of Fire, Part 1: The Windomills

description: The most downloaded comic series ever, "Freshman Year," returns in an expanded saga with the same powerhouse team that took it to the top. In this issue, Chuck's past comes back to haunt him when rumor has it that Riverdale dropout-turned-rapper 60 Cent isn't too happy with the cartoonist's latest success. Now Chuck must seek the help of friends from his freshman year to find a way to survive through the next one!
name: Freshman Year - the Missing Chapters: Chuck
Heart of Fire, Part 2: All The Flesh Inherits
Heart of Fire, Part 3: In The Blind Days

description:
"The Staff": A new chauffeur is driving Veronica... and Veronica and her friends are driving him crazy!
"Picture This": Chuck and Nancy make a picture-perfect couple - even when they both enter the same teen arts competition! But is it possible Nancy's snap shot has a chance against Chuck's painstakingly perfect painting?
"Bee Crazy": After a week of detention, Reggie has "The Bee" constantly buzzing through his brain! Will he ever escape the looming presence of Mr. Weatherbee?
name: The Staff

description:
"Ham(burger) to the Chief!": It's a colossal comedy of errors... topped with ketchup and pickles... when Archie is convinced the President of the United States is coming to town to visit the new burger joint!

"Gag Drag": After pulling off countless pranks, Reggie's come down with a case of "jokester's block!" Has the king of tricks fallen from his throne?
name: Ham(burger) to the Chief

description:
IT'S THE MILESTONE 200th issue of VERONICA!

"It's Good to Be 200!": In her 200th anniversary issue, Veronica chooses a destination to top any when she uses Dilton and Marcy's new time machine to travel back to Riverdale's past... but staying too long could alter that history forever! It's a time-tripping anniversary issue you just can't afford to miss!
name: It's Good To Be 200!

description: The next thrilling chapter in the ElfQuest saga begins in this all-new bimonthly miniseries by Wendy and Richard Pini! Cutter's son Sunbeam has been hibernating, but his soul self has been exploring the world of Two Moons. He has made contact with an underwater tribe, one that fears all life on the surface. When Sunbeam experiences Recognition with one of the sea denizens, he leads his fellow Wolfriders on the beginning of a new journey, one promising discovery, danger and romance! Â

The all-new bimonthly miniseries continues! Sunstream is awake and ready to lead the Wolfriders to the distant sea, and the Wave Dancers. While Brill can't wait to meet her recognized partner in the flesh, not every underwater denizen is as eager.

At last the Wolfriders and WaveDancers meet! As Sunstream and Brill finally celebrate their Recognition, Surge tests the limits of his power to prevent the WaveDancers from entering the Crystal Palace. But when Wolfrider chief Cutter tries to reason with Surge, not all the Palace's magic can prevent what happens next.

The miniseries conclusion! Chief versus chief. Father versus son. The Wolfriders are helpless as WaveDancer Snakeskin duels with his own sire to free Cutter and regain leadership of his own clan. But there's far more at stake than anyone realizes when nature itself strikes back! Â

The first new ElfQuest material in years, now available in a softcover edition! In this stunning tale, the elves must adapt to a world without the Troll smiths, who forged their weapons and tools. Painfully aware of her human heritage, Shuna embarks on a quest to unite elves and humans in peace.Â  Â
name: The Searcher & the Sword

volume.name: Elfquest: The Searcher and the Sword

description: GrimJack is in a race to save Blacjac and Bob from the Manx Cat. The problem is everyone who falls asleep becomes an unwilling Night Terrorist in the Manx Cat's army! Bullets, blood, bikes, bombastic babes and the St. John Knives! What more can you want in a stunning conclusion?
